value.name: BMW 326 - Wikipedia
value.snippet: The BMW 326 is a medium-sized sedan produced by BMW between 1936 and 1941, [3] and again briefly, under Soviet control, after 1945. The 326 was BMW's first four-door sedan. [4] It had an innovative design and sold well despite its relatively high price. It also had an unusually involved afterlife.

value.name: 326Power | 326Power USA
value.snippet: 326Power USA is the offical sister company to 326Power Japan. 326 Power is also know as Mitsuru Power here in Japan and is world famous for the multi-coloured mad max style lug nut caps. 326Power also makes a ton of other JDM parts such as colourful lug nuts, wide body kits, calipers and coilovers.
